Package: dosefitr
Type: Package
Title: Dose-Response Curve Fitting for 'NanoBRET' and Cell Viability
        Assays
Version: 1.0.0
Authors@R: 
    person("Thiago", "Loreto Matos", 
           email = "thiago-loreto@hotmail.com", 
           role = c("aut", "cre", "cph"))
Description: End-to-end dose-response analysis pipeline for 'NanoBRET' kinase
    binding assays and cell viability experiments. Reads raw 'BMG PHERAstar'
    plate-reader exports, computes BRET ratios, detects and removes outliers
    using the ROUT method of Motulsky and Brown (2006) <doi:10.1186/1471-2105-7-123>,
    and fits three- or four-parameter logistic models to derive IC50 and pIC50
    values with confidence intervals. Provides automatic quality control metrics
    (Z-prime, assay window, signal-to-background, CV percent), batch processing
    across multiple plates, outlier visualisation, multi-compound overlay plots,
    and plate-comparison plots. Exports results to Excel and generates
    'Scarab'-formatted tables for 'NanoBRET' kinase profiling data submission.
